ZCZC EE94
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 252300 UTC
ON THURSDAY EVENING A LARGE AND COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WITH MULTIPLE
CENTRES WILL BE SITUATED OVER THE MID-ATLANTIC WITH ASSOCIATED FRONTAL
SYSTEMS MOV NEWARDS ACROSS THE UK. THE COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IS LIKELY
TO REMAIN SITUATED TO THE NW OF THE UK ON FRIDAY WITH ONE CENTRE 991 LOCATED
TO THE N OF SCOTLAND. HOWEVER THERE IS SIG UNCERTAINTY IN THE LOCATION OF
ANY LOW CENTRES SATURDAY AND SUNDAY ALTHOUGH THE COMPLEXITY OF THE LOW PRESSURE
SYSTEM WILL REMAIN CLOSE TO THE N AND W OF THE UK. A SWATHE OF STRG WINDS
ARE LIKELY TO AFFECT ALL NITON SEA AREAS THURSDAY EVENING WITH RISK OF GALES
MAINLY FITZROY AND SOLE BEFORE EXTENDING INTO CELTIC SEA AND IRISH SEA AREAS
OVERNIGHT INTO FRIDAY MORNING. WINDS EASING FRIDAY AFTERNOON ALTHOUGH ANOTHER
SWATHE OF STRG WINDS ARE POSS IN FITZROY AND SOLE. UNCERTAINTY IN EXACT LOCATION
OF STRG WINDS SATURDAY AND SUNDAY ALTHOUGH NEAR GALE OR GALES POSS
